  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "F6v_1wHtG2nS"
   },
   "source": [
    "**Project Summary:**\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Unveiling Insights from Tata Steel's Operational Data: An Exploratory Analysis**\n",
    "\n",
    "This project embarks on a detailed exploratory data analysis (EDA) of Tata Steel's operational dataset, aiming to extract valuable insights that can inform strategic business decisions. Through an in-depth examination of trends, patterns, and correlations, we strive to enhance the understanding of key operational factors affecting efficiency and performance.\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Phase 1: Data Cleaning and Preprocessing**\n",
    "Raw operational data often contains inconsistencies, missing values, and outliers, which can impact analytical accuracy. To address this, we will implement techniques such as:\n",
    "- **Data Imputation** – Handling missing values effectively to maintain data integrity.\n",
    "- **Outlier Detection** – Identifying and managing extreme values that may distort analysis.\n",
    "- **Data Transformation** – Standardizing and normalizing data to ensure consistency.\n",
    "\n",
    "This foundational step ensures the dataset is refined and ready for accurate interpretation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Phase 2: Understanding Data Structure and Distribution**\n",
    "Once the data is preprocessed, we will explore its structure and key characteristics. Descriptive statistics such as mean, median, standard deviation, and percentiles will be calculated for major variables to provide an overview of their distribution. To visualize these metrics, we will use:\n",
    "- **Histograms** – To analyze frequency distributions and detect skewness.\n",
    "- **Box Plots** – To identify variability and potential outliers in numerical variables.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Phase 3: Data Segmentation and Comparative Analysis**\n",
    "To gain a more granular understanding, we will segment the data based on relevant factors such as production units, product categories, and time periods. This segmentation will allow us to:\n",
    "- Compare operational efficiency across different divisions.\n",
    "- Identify strengths and weaknesses in various production processes.\n",
    "\n",
    "Bar charts and pie charts will be used to present these segmented insights effectively.\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Phase 4: Relationship Analysis**\n",
    "Scatter plots and correlation matrices will be used to explore relationships between key operational variables. This will help uncover:\n",
    "- **Potential dependencies** between variables such as raw material input and finished product output.\n",
    "- **Non-linear associations** that may impact machine performance.\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Key Objectives:**\n",
    "- **Predictive Maintenance:** Implement machine learning models to anticipate potential machine failures, reducing unplanned downtime.\n",
    "- **Data-Driven Insights:** Identify correlations between operational factors and machine failure to support informed decision-making.\n",
    "- **Performance Optimization:** Leverage data analytics to fine-tune machine parameters for enhanced efficiency.\n",
    "- **Operational Efficiency Improvement:** Pinpoint system vulnerabilities to ensure peak machine performance, thereby boosting overall productivity.\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Approach:**\n",
    "1. **Data Collection & Preprocessing:**\n",
    "   - Gather operational data, including metrics like temperature, speed, torque, and wear.\n",
    "   - Handle missing values, encode categorical variables, and normalize numerical features.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA):**\n",
    "   - Visualize data distribution and inter-variable relationships using statistical graphs such as histograms, box plots, scatter plots, and correlation matrices.\n",
    "   - Analyze trends and segment-specific insights to drive actionable recommendations.\n",
    "\n",
    "Through this structured approach, we aim to extract meaningful insights that can drive operational improvements and enhance Tata Steel’s overall productivity.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },

    "#### **Define Your Business Objective?**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "PhDvGCAqmjP1"
   },
   "source": [
    "Problem Statement:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.Tata Steel's core challenge is to develop predictive models that can accurately forecast machine failures using operational data. This allows for proactive maintenance, minimizing unplanned downtime and ensuring continuous production.\n",
    "\n",
    "2.By preventing machine failures, Tata Steel aims to improve overall production efficiency, reduce maintenance costs, and consistently maintain high product quality. The focus is on leveraging data to enhance operational performance.\n",
    "\n",
    "3.The company wants to utilize advanced data analytics and machine learning techniques on a synthetically generated dataset to gain actionable insights into machine behavior and failure patterns, thereby enabling data-driven decision-making for maintenance and operational strategies.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Business Objective:\n",
    " By leveraging data analytics and exploratory data analysis (EDA), Tata Steel aims to reduce downtime, minimize maintenance costs, and enhance production efficiency. This proactive approach will help optimize resource utilization, improve machinery reliability, and ensure consistent product quality, ultimately leading to higher operational efficiency and cost savings."
   ]

    "  You can set up factory or industry at a cool place for more productivity to main less heat dissipation failure [HDF].\n",

    "4.Tool wear > 200 increases the chances of Tool wear failure.\n",
    "5.If torque lies between 20 and 60, chances of PWF (Power failure) is less.\n",
    "6.Chances of OSF (Overstrain failure) is less if tool wear values lie between 25 and 150 and torque < 45.\n",
